# cli-anything-hanes

CLI harness for **HANES MES** (Wire Harness Manufacturing Execution System).

Wraps the HANES MES REST API into a Click-based CLI with REPL support,
enabling AI agents and power users to operate the MES without a browser.

## Prerequisites

- **Python 3.10+**
- **HANES MES Backend** running on `localhost:3003`
  ```bash
  cd C:\Project\HANES\apps\backend
  pnpm dev
  ```

## Installation

```bash
cd C:\Project\HANES\agent-harness
pip install -e .
```

## Verify Installation

```bash
cli-anything-hanes --version
cli-anything-hanes --help
```

## Usage

### One-shot commands

```bash
# Login
cli-anything-hanes auth login -e admin@hanes.com -p password

# List parts (human-readable table)
cli-anything-hanes master parts

# List job orders in JSON mode (for agents)
cli-anything-hanes --json production orders --status RUNNING

# Show dashboard KPI
cli-anything-hanes dashboard kpi
```

### Interactive REPL

```bash
# Just run without subcommand to enter REPL
cli-anything-hanes
```

### JSON mode (for AI agents)

All commands support `--json` for machine-readable output:

```bash
cli-anything-hanes --json master parts --search "wire"
cli-anything-hanes --json production orders --status WAITING
cli-anything-hanes --json quality reworks
```

## Command Groups

| Group        | Description                    |
|-------------|-------------------------------|
| `auth`       | Login, logout, session status  |
| `master`     | Parts, processes, BOM, routing |
| `material`   | Arrivals, lots, stocks         |
| `production` | Job orders, results            |
| `quality`    | Inspections, reworks, defects  |
| `inventory`  | Stocks, transactions           |
| `dashboard`  | KPI and summaries              |

## Running Tests

```bash
cd C:\Project\HANES\agent-harness
python -m pytest cli_anything/hanes/tests/ -v -s
```

## Architecture

```
CLI (Click + REPL)
  -> hanes_backend.py (urllib HTTP client)
    -> HANES MES Backend API (NestJS, port 3003)
      -> Oracle Database
```

The CLI is a **client** to the running HANES MES backend. It does NOT
connect directly to the database — all operations go through the REST API.
